      "body": "**Stacks 04KV/037Q descent CLOSED** \u2014 `geometricallyConnected_of_connected_of_section` is axiom-clean (T5, run 0005 session 0007).\n\n- New module `AlgebraicJacobian/Picard/GeometricallyConnectedSection.lean` (~330 LOC, Mathlib-only imports, sorry-free, axioms = propext/choice/Quot.sound): Stacks 05P3 (`A \u2297[k] B` domain over alg-closed `k`, via Nullstellensatz-evaluation + Jacobson-radical coordinate argument + f.g.-subalgebra exhaustion), then geometry: fibers of `X_L \u2192 X` are `Spec(K \u2297 L)`; alg-closed base via Mathlib's `GeometricallyConnected.connectedSpace`; algebraic-closure step via open+closed(integral)+singleton-fiber clopen argument; assembly `k \u2286 k\u0304 \u21aa L\u0304 \u2287 L`.\n- Key Mathlib enablers already present in v4.31: `UniversallyOpen` instance for morphisms to Spec-of-field (Stacks 0383), `IsIntegralHom \u2192 UniversallyClosed`, the `geometrically` framework, `Scheme.Hom.fiber` API, `descResidueField_stalkClosedPointTo_fromSpecResidueField` for the section retraction.\n- `identityComponent_geometricallyConnected` is now axiom-clean automatically. IdentityComponent sorries: 9 \u2192 8.\n- **Unblocked next**: `baseChangeIso` iso slot (clopen-image identification, ~80-100 LOC per in-file plan) and `isSubgroupHomomorphism` (`G\u2070 \u00d7\u2096 G\u2070` connected now derivable via the Mathlib pullback instance). Remaining Pic\u2070-specific sorries still FGA-blocked.\n- **Stale mirror**: `SubProjects/Picard-IdentityComponent` is now BEHIND AJC (was byte-identical); re-sync needs `IdentityComponent.lean` + the new `GeometricallyConnectedSection.lean` + blueprint chapter.",
