      "body": "**Reconcile of run 0006 T6 (Albanese dead-code cleanup): verified clean \u2014 but the `ALB.codim1` proof leg is now fully upstream-blocked.**\n\n- **T6 work is correct and green.** `lake build` exits 0 (8581 jobs); the ~256-LOC superseded MvPolynomial-height chain was deleted (all `private`, no consumers), 9 dead blueprint nodes pruned/re-pointed, `horizon blueprint` shows Albanese **0 dangling**. Sorry set unchanged.\n\n- **No reachable proof work remains on `ALB.codim1`.** Its 4 residual sorries are all gated on API absent from Mathlib v4.31 \u2014 Stacks **00OF** (regular localisation), **0AVF** (depth-2 $H^1$ vanishing), and the **Milne 3.3** function-field-pullback bridge. Re-running `horizon run ALB.codim1` will not progress without a large homological build or a Mathlib bump.\n\n- **Recommendation:** point the next Albanese-adjacent slot at the reachable frontier instead \u2014 `AJC.pic0av` (tangent-space $T_e\\cong H^1$ comparison) or `AJC.picrep`/FGA representability. Fixed one stale index number en passant (`Thm32` \\times 2 \u2192 \\times 1).",
